    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\n Commerce Basics\n Get Started with Salesforce Commerce\n Import and Export Commerce Data\n Access to Commerce Stores\n Products and Pricing\n Catalogs for a Store\n Product Categories\n Products\n Add a Product to a Commerce Store\n Enhance a Product Description with Einstein\n Enhance Product Fields with Einstein\n Product Image Types\n Add Media to Products and Categories\n Add Products to Categories\n Choose Product Categories to Use in Breadcrumbs\n Purchase Quantity Rules for a B2B Store\n Product Variations and Attributes\n Add Product Variations and Attributes with Guided Setup\n Product Classes, Variations, and Attributes\n Create Attributes for Product Variations\n Add an Attribute Set to a Product\n Make Product Variations and Variation Attributes Searchable\n Product Variation Grouping\n Entitlement Policies\n Product Sets\n Pricing for Commerce Stores\n Configure Checkout for a Commerce Store\n Store Search\n Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for Commerce\n Commerce Einstein\n Einstein and Data Usage in Commerce Cloud\n Data Cloud for Commerce\n Store Management\n Commerce Promotions\n Sell Globally\n Website Design for Commerce Stores\n Publication and Activation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nB2B COMMERCE AND D2C COMMERCE\nMake Product Variations and Variation Attributes Searchable\n\nSet up Search for product variations and variation attributes so that they’re discoverable in your store.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience and Salesforce mobile app\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nAvailable in: B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nIMPORTANT As of Summer ’24, there’s a refreshed Commerce app, which we encourage you to use. The navigation steps in this Help documentation reflect the new app. If you’re still using the previous app, now called the Commerce Storefront Console, see B2B and D2C Commerce Using the Commerce Storefront Console. For instructions on switching to the refreshed app, see Enable the Refreshed Commerce App.\nAdd product attributes as searchable fields so that they’re included in search indexing.\nIn the navigation sidebar, select a store from the Store dropdown.\nClick Search.\nOn the Search page, select the Searchable Fields tab, and then click Manage Searchable Fields.\nSelect the fields that you want to make searchable, and click Save.\nAdd attributes as search filters so that they’re visible as facets on results and category pages.\nGo back to the Search page, and open the Results Filters tab.\nClick Manage Filters.\nMove the attributes to use as search filters to the Selected Fields list.\nArrange the list, and click Save.\nAdd the Variation Attributes field to the Results Layout component.\nIn Experience Builder, open the Search Results page.\nSelect the Results Layout component.\nIn the property editor, click Add Field.\nClick the added field.\nIn Edit Field, change the field value to Variation Attributes.\nAdjust the other properties as needed.\nSave your changes.\nRepeat these steps on the Category Detail page.\nRebuild your store’s search index.\nReturn to the Search page, and open the Search Index Summary tab.\nClick Rebuild Index, and then click Rebuild.\nSEE ALSO\nProduct Variations and Attributes\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
